    708          /**
    709           *    @brief    This method handles internal voltage reference in order to check A/D accuracy and proper multiplexing.
    710           *    @details  On every call it verifies the ADCx Engine by reading the Internal power block.
    711           *              This method should be called periodically or as per application requirement to ensure the ADCx Engine is working.
    712           *    @retval PASS : ADC value read from the "Internal Power Block" is in range
    713           *    @retval FAIL : ADC value read from the "Internal Power Block" is out of range
    714           */
